Template: ssh/use_old_init_script
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you want to continue (and risk killing active ssh sessions)?
 The version of /etc/init.d/ssh that you have installed, is likely to kill
 all running sshd instances.  If you are doing this upgrade via an ssh
 session, that would be a Bad Thing(tm).
 .
 You can fix this by adding "--pidfile /var/run/sshd.pid" to the
 start-stop-daemon line in the stop section of the file.
Description-ca: Esteu segur de voler continuar (tot i la possibilitat d'aturar les sessions d'ssh actives)?
 La versiσ de l'/etc/init.d/ssh que heu instalΖlat probablement aturarύ les
 instύncies de l'sshd que s'estan executant. Si esteu realitzant
 l'actualitzaciσ de de d'una sessiσ d'ssh us podria penjar la connexiσ.
 .
 Ho podeu arreglar afegint la lμnia "--pidfile /var/run/sshd.pid" a la
 lμnia start-stop-daemon de la secciσ stop del fitxer.
Description-cs: Chcete pokraηovat (a riskovat ukonηenμ aktivnμch ssh spojenμ)?
 Stαvajμcμ verze /etc/init.d/ssh pravdλpadobnλ pozabμjμ vΙechny bλΨμcμ
 instance sshd. Pokud tuto aktualizaci provαdμte pχes ssh, byla by to
 ©patnα Vλc(tm).
 .
